<TITLE>avilistopened</TITLE>
<TYPE>SIVP Toolbox</TYPE>
<DATE>April, 2006</DATE>
<SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="avilistopened">Show all opened video files. (experimental)</SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
<CALLING_SEQUENCE>
   <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>I=avilistopened()</CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
</CALLING_SEQUENCE>
<PARAM>
<PARAM_INDENT>
   <PARAM_ITEM>
   <PARAM_NAME>I</PARAM_NAME>
   <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
   A vector, the opened video file/camera indices.
   </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
   </PARAM_ITEM>
</PARAM_INDENT>
</PARAM>

<DESCRIPTION>
<P>
   <TT>avilistopened</TT>list all opened files and cameras.
</P>
<P>
Video support for SIVP is only available when SIVP is compiled with OpenCV which support video I/O.
</P>
</DESCRIPTION>
<EXAMPLE><![CDATA[
	
    n = aviopen(SCI+'/contrib/sivp/images/video.avi');
    im = avireadframe(n); //get a frame
    imshow(im);

    avilistopened()
    aviclose(n);

]]></EXAMPLE>
